              "label": "Gamified Intervention",
              "type": "EXPERIMENTAL",
              "description": "This condition involved the implementation of an assistive technology software (the MapHabit system) with added gamification features into the daily care of the participants. The experimental condition received the version that incorporates gamified content and structure. Gamification involved receiving four new cognitive games each month. The cognitive games that were chosen for the current study followed game types observed to be prevalent in literature centered on serious games within dementia research. These games aim for cognitive stimulation in slowing down symptom acuity. Game design elements of positive reinforcement, problem-solving, progression, and visual cues were implemented into game content and software.",
              "interventionNames": [
