              "description": "Rating of paratonia severity by means of the Modified Ashworth Scale (MAS). Resistance against passive movement of the limbs is rated. Scores: 0: Normal tone, passive movement no problem; 1: Mild paratonia, slight resistance in passive movement; 2: Moderate paratonia, enhanced resistance in passive movement; 3: Severe paratonia, severe resistance in passive movement; 4: Very severe paratonia, passive movement (almost) impossible. Participants with moderate to severe paratonia were included in this study, defined as presence of a MAS score of ≥2 in at least one limb",
